<!--January (Lunisolar)-->

{{Lunisolar January}} '''''Zhēngyuè''''' is the first [[month]] of the [[year]] in the [[Chinese calendar]]. In general, the Vernal Showers are in Zhēngyuè. The name comes from the annual [[morale]]-building [[Li (Confucian)|rite]] ({{zh|c=正旦大朝}}) in [[ancient China]].
Zhēngyuè 1 is the [[day]] of the [[rooster]]; Zhēngyuè 2 is the day of the [[dog]]; Zhēngyuè 3 is the day of the [[pig]]; Zhēngyuè 4 is the day of the [[goat]]; Zhēngyuè 5 is the day of the [[ox]]; Zhēngyuè 6 is the day of the [[horse]]; Zhēngyuè 7 is the day of the [[human]].
'''Lunisolar January''' (旧暦一月) is the first {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|12=draft|12=draft}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|1=Lunisolar calendar|2=ja|3=太陰太陽暦|comment=note that this is not the Japanese lunisolar calendar it is any lunisolar calendar|4=ru|5=Лунно-солнечный календарь|6=de|7=Lunisolarkalender|8=es|9=Calendario lunisolar|10=fr|11=Calendrier luni-solaire|12=draft|12=draft}}).
Under definitions predating the {{ill|Tenpō Calendar|ja|天保暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, January was defined as the month that includes {{ill|Rain Water|ja|雨水|1=Yushui (solar term)|lt=Yushui|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the {{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦|1=New Calendar (Japan)|lt=New Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|January|ja|1月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to early {{ill|March|ja|3月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Another name for January is '''Mutsuki''' (睦月). For the origin of the name, see {{ill|January|ja|1月|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
In the Eastern lunisolar calendar, the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days) varies from year to year. As a result, there are years when January ends on the 29th, with no January 30th.
