{{Lunisolar January|qq=}} '''''Zhēngyuè''''' is the first [[month]] of the [[year]] in the [[Chinese calendar]]. In general, the Vernal Showers are in Zhēngyuè. The name comes from the annual [[morale]]-building [[Li (Confucian)|rite]] ({{zh|c=正旦大朝|qq=}}) in [[ancient China]].
Zhēngyuè 1 is the [[day]] of the [[rooster]]; Zhēngyuè 2 is the day of the [[dog]]; Zhēngyuè 3 is the day of the [[pig]]; Zhēngyuè 4 is the day of the [[goat]]; Zhēngyuè 5 is the day of the [[ox]]; Zhēngyuè 6 is the day of the [[horse]]; Zhēngyuè 7 is the day of the [[human]].
'''Lunisolar January''' (旧暦一月) is the first {{ill|Month (Calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|lt=Month|lt_ja=月|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} of the year in the {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ({{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|太陰太陽暦|1=Lunisolar calendar|2=ja|3=太陰太陽暦|comment=note that this is not the Japanese lunisolar calendar it is any lunisolar calendar|4=ru|5=Лунно-солнечный календарь|6=de|7=Lunisolarkalender|8=es|9=Calendario lunisolar|10=fr|11=Calendrier luni-solaire|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}).
Under definitions predating the {{ill|Tenpō Calendar|ja|天保暦|qq=draft|qq=}}, January was defined as the month that includes {{ill|Rain Water|ja|雨水|1=Yushui (solar term)|lt=Yushui|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the {{ill|New Calendar|ja|新暦|1=New Calendar (Japan)|lt=New Calendar|qq=draft|qq=}}, it corresponds approximately to late {{ill|January|ja|1月|qq=draft|qq=}} to early {{ill|March|ja|3月|qq=draft|qq=}}.
Another name for January is '''Mutsuki''' (睦月). The etymology is explained at [[#Etymology of traditional Japanese name]]
In the Eastern lunisolar calendar, the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|qq=draft|qq=}}, (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days) varies from year to year. As a result, there are years when January ends on the 29th, with no January 30th.
==Etymology of traditional Japanese name== {{afc comment|1=content here taken from [[:ja:1月]][[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:08, 11 May 2025 (UTC)}} In {{ill|Japan|ja|日本}}, the '''Lunar January''' is called '''Mutsuki''' (むつき), and today it is also used as an alternate name for January of the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|新暦}}. There are various theories about the origin of the name Mutsuki. The most widely accepted theory holds that it derives from “Mutsubizuki” (睦び月), meaning “month of harmony,” when all relatives gather to hold banquets. Other theories include “Mototsuki” (元つ月), “Moyutsuki” (萌月), and “Umutsuki” (生月).
In the Saru dialect of the {{ill|Hokkaido Ainu language|ja|北海道アイヌ語}}, it is called “Towetanne” (トウエタンネ; {{ill|Ainu language|ja|アイヌ語}}: towetanne), meaning “the days become longer” (<ref>{{Cite web |title=アイヌ語カレンダー |url=https://www.ff-ainu.or.jp/calendardownload.html |website=(公益財団法人 アイヌ民族文化財団) |access-date=2025-01-12}}</ref>), and in the Asahikawa dialect, January is called “Inomi Cup” (イノミチュㇷ゚; {{ill|Ainu language|ja|アイヌ語}}: inomi cup), meaning “month of praying to the gods” (<ref>{{Cite web |title=月刊シロㇿ 10月号（2015.10） |url=https://ainugo.nam.go.jp/siror/monthly/201510.html#01 |website=アイヌと自然 デジタル図鑑 |access-date=2025-01-09 |publisher={{ill|Ainu Museum|ja|アイヌ民族博物館}}}}</ref>). == Dates in Mutsuki == {| class="wikitable" |+ Dates in Mutsuki ! Year !! New Moon !! Last Day !! Number of Days |- | 2014 || {{ill|January 31|ja|1月31日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|February 28|ja|2月28日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2015 || {{ill|February 19|ja|2月19日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 19|ja|3月19日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2016 || {{ill|February 8|ja|2月8日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 8|ja|3月8日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2017 || {{ill|January 28|ja|1月28日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|February 25|ja|2月25日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2018 || {{ill|February 16|ja|2月16日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 16|ja|3月16日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2019 || {{ill|February 5|ja|2月5日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 6|ja|3月6日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2020 || {{ill|January 25|ja|1月25日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|February 23|ja|2月23日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2021 || {{ill|February 12|ja|2月12日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 12|ja|3月12日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2022 || {{ill|February 1|ja|2月1日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 2|ja|3月2日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2023 || {{ill|January 22|ja|1月22日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|February 19|ja|2月19日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2024 || {{ill|February 10|ja|2月10日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|March 9|ja|3月9日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2025 || {{ill|January 29|ja|1月29日|qq=draft|qq=}} || {{ill|February 27|ja|2月27日|qq=draft|qq=}} || 30 days |}
