In the Eastern lunisolar calendar, the number of days in a month, known as {{ill|Large and Small|ja|大小|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Large and Small|qq=}}, (with large months having 30 days and small months 29 days) varies from year to year. As a result, there are years when January ends on the 29th, with no January 30th.
==Etymology of traditional Japanese name== {{afc comment|1=content here taken from [[:ja:1月]][[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:08, 11 May 2025 (UTC)}} In {{ill|Japan|ja|日本|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japan|qq=}}, the '''Lunar January''' is called '''Mutsuki''' (むつき), and today it is also used as an alternate name for January of the {{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|新暦|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}}. There are various theories about the origin of the name Mutsuki. The most widely accepted theory holds that it derives from “Mutsubizuki” (睦び月), meaning “month of harmony,” when all relatives gather to hold banquets. Other theories include “Mototsuki” (元つ月), “Moyutsuki” (萌月), and “Umutsuki” (生月).
In the Saru dialect of the {{ill|Hokkaido Ainu language|ja|北海道アイヌ語|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokkaido Ainu language|qq=}}, it is called “Towetanne” (トウエタンネ; {{ill|Ainu language|ja|アイヌ語|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ainu language|qq=}}: towetanne), meaning “the days become longer” (<ref>{{Cite web |title=アイヌ語カレンダー |url=https://www.ff-ainu.or.jp/calendardownload.html |website=(公益財団法人 アイヌ民族文化財団) |access-date=2025-01-12}}</ref>), and in the Asahikawa dialect, January is called “Inomi Cup” (イノミチュㇷ゚; {{ill|Ainu language|ja|アイヌ語|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ainu language|qq=}}: inomi cup), meaning “month of praying to the gods” (<ref>{{Cite web |title=月刊シロㇿ 10月号（2015.10） |url=https://ainugo.nam.go.jp/siror/monthly/201510.html#01 |website=アイヌと自然 デジタル図鑑 |access-date=2025-01-09 |publisher={{ill|Ainu Museum|ja|アイヌ民族博物館|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ainu Museum|qq=}}}}</ref>). == Dates in Mutsuki == {| class="wikitable" |+ Dates in Mutsuki ! Year !! New Moon !! Last Day !! Number of Days |- | 2014 || {{ill|January 31|ja|1月31日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/January 31|qq=}} || {{ill|February 28|ja|2月28日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 28|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2015 || {{ill|February 19|ja|2月19日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 19|qq=}} || {{ill|March 19|ja|3月19日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 19|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2016 || {{ill|February 8|ja|2月8日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 8|qq=}} || {{ill|March 8|ja|3月8日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 8|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2017 || {{ill|January 28|ja|1月28日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/January 28|qq=}} || {{ill|February 25|ja|2月25日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 25|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2018 || {{ill|February 16|ja|2月16日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 16|qq=}} || {{ill|March 16|ja|3月16日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 16|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2019 || {{ill|February 5|ja|2月5日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 5|qq=}} || {{ill|March 6|ja|3月6日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 6|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2020 || {{ill|January 25|ja|1月25日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/January 25|qq=}} || {{ill|February 23|ja|2月23日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 23|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2021 || {{ill|February 12|ja|2月12日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 12|qq=}} || {{ill|March 12|ja|3月12日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 12|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2022 || {{ill|February 1|ja|2月1日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 1|qq=}} || {{ill|March 2|ja|3月2日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 2|qq=}} || 30 days |- | 2023 || {{ill|January 22|ja|1月22日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/January 22|qq=}} || {{ill|February 19|ja|2月19日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 19|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2024 || {{ill|February 10|ja|2月10日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 10|qq=}} || {{ill|March 9|ja|3月9日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March 9|qq=}} || 29 days |- | 2025 || {{ill|January 29|ja|1月29日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/January 29|qq=}} || {{ill|February 27|ja|2月27日|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/February 27|qq=}} || 30 days |}
== Overview == {{unreferenced|date=January 2015|qq=}} {{Italic title|reason=|qq=}}
==Festivals== *[[Chinese New Year|New Year's Day]] ({{zh|c=春节|qq=}}) is Zhēngyuè 1. The following New Year's Day is January 29, 2025, which is a statutory [[holiday]]. *The [[Yuanxiao Festival]] ({{zh|c=元宵|qq=}}) is Zhēngyuè 15. The following Yuanxiao is February 12, 2025.
==Birth== *[[Wu Zetian]], the only [[female]] [[emperor]] of [[China]], Zhēngyuè 23, 624 *[[Li Bai]], a Chinese [[poet]] acclaimed to this day as a [[genius]] and romantic figure who took traditional [[poetry|poetic]] forms to new heights, Zhēngyuè 16, 701 *[[Emperor Shunzong of Tang]], an emperor of the Chinese [[Tang dynasty]], Zhēngyuè 12, 761 *[[Bai Juyi]], a Chinese [[poet]] of the Tang dynasty, Zhēngyuè 20, 772 *[[Emperor Xizong of Jin]], an emperor of the [[Jin dynasty (1115–1234)|Jin dynasty]] which controlled northern China from 1115 to 1234, Zhēngyuè 17, 1119 *[[Qiu Chuji]], a [[Daoist]] of [[Wang Chongyang]], Zhēngyuè 9, 1148 *[[Itō Suketaka]], a samurai, daimyō and twelfth family leader of the Itō clan, Zhēngyuè 15, 1559 *[[Li Hongzhang]], a [[politician]], [[general]], and [[diplomat]] of the late [[Qing Empire]], Zhēngyuè 5, 1823 *[[Aisin-Gioro Puyi]], the last emperor of China and the twelfth and final ruler of the [[Qing dynasty]], Zhēngyuè 14, 1906
==Death== *[[Sun Jian]], a military general and [[warlord]] who lived in the late [[Eastern Han dynasty]], Zhēngyuè 7, 191 *[[Guan Yu]], a general serving under the warlord [[Liu Bei]] in the late Eastern Han dynasty, Zhēngyuè 13, 220 *[[Cao Cao]], a warlord and the penultimate [[chancellor]] of the Eastern Han dynasty who rose to great power in the final years of the dynasty, Zhēngyuè 23, 220 *[[Emperor Xianzong of Tang]], an emperor of the Chinese Tang dynasty, Zhēngyuè 27, 820 *[[Emperor Yingzong of Song]], the fifth emperor of the [[Song dynasty]] of China, Zhēngyuè 7, 1067 *[[Emperor Zhezong of Song]], the seventh emperor of the Song dynasty of China, Zhēngyuè 12, 1100 *[[Kublai Khan]], the fifth [[Khagan]] (Great Khan) of the Ikh Mongol Uls ([[Mongol Empire]]), [[reign]]ing from 1260 to 1294, and the founder of the [[Yuan dynasty]] in [[Mongolia]] and China, Zhēngyuè 22, 1294 *[[Shunzhi Emperor]], the third emperor of the Qing dynasty and the first Qing emperor to rule over China, from 1644 to 1661, Zhēngyuè 30, 1638 *[[Qianlong Emperor]], the sixth emperor of the [[Manchu]]-led Qing dynasty, and the fourth Qing emperor to rule over China proper, Zhēngyuè 3, 1799 *[[Daoguang Emperor]], a Qing emperor, Zhēngyuè 14, 1850
